{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "SparseDrive [35] uses a sparse-centric pipeline to get rid of BEV features in the E2E driving pipeline, and DiffusionDrive [32] designs a truncated denoising scheme for the diffusion model to generate multi-mode motion trajectories.",
    "With the prosperity of foundation models, a series of works [36,37,38,39,40] incorporate Large Language Models (LLMs) and Vision-Language Models (VLMs) into the E2E planning pipeline.",
    "Despite the benefits of commonsense reasoning with foundation models, most of the existing models still focus on the open-loop evaluation or the approximate closed-loop metrics from the open-loop evaluation [22], which lack counterfactual reasoning for the safety-critical scenarios.",
    "A recent work RAD [19] pays attention to the photorealistic closed-loop evaluation and utilizes imitation learning and online reinforcement learning to fine-tune the E2E driving agents.",
    "Yet, the value functions trained for the Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) agents are not effectively integrated during the inference."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
